Another great leg day done. Box squats are a great way to train legs and glutes. 
This is just one of the exercises i incorporated into todays routine and I enjoyed the intense pump I got from it 
Try it … it’s good for you 🦵🏼🦵🏼🦵🏼🦵🏼🦵🏼🦵🏼

The box squat is exactly like a standard squat, except that there is a dedicated pause at the bottom of the movement. It involves using a knee-height box that allows you to lower yourself until your thighs are relatively parallel with the ground. 

Box squats work your posterior chain. When performing box squats, extend your lower body back further than you would during a regular squat. This movement pattern helps to activate muscle groups across your lower body, including your hamstrings, glutes, spinal erectors, hip flexors, and lower back muscles.

I wasn’t going to post this video. 
I weigh 160lbs and the dumbbell weighed 120lbs
My form was as good as I could get it considering the length of the dumbbell vs the length of my torso 
I usually stick with lighter weights to get proper form and better muscle contraction. However sometimes a bit of “powerlifting” can help with strength building. 
I wanted to see if I could do it … single arm dumbbell rows require a lot of core, lower back and shoulder strength even though the primary muscles being worked are the back muscles. 
It was nice to shock my muscles a bit with this heavy lift.  But I do prefer good form and full range of motion. 
It is nice to know I could row 120lbs a few times with one arm 💪 because I remember when training with 2lb .. 5lb and 8lb dumbbells felt like a killer workout

Training is not just about moving the weight you lift for a number of reps. Training is 
the mind to muscle connection 
The range of motion 
The speed of motion
The angle 
The muscle contraction 
The focus on the negative and the positive aspect of motion 
It is about your strength, health, nutrition, supplementation, rest, recovery, balance, coordination, endurance, flexibility and conditioning 
What you see in the mirror is the sum of the attention you give to all of these elements 
Training is not just going to the gym everyday 
It’s focusing your mind so that your body performs and provides results 
#strongmind #strongbody

I love performing dumbbell pullovers as a warmup exercise on upper body days involving back, chest and shoulders 

This exercise really helps to get my muscles warmed up, stretched, primed and ready for heavier movements 

Pullovers also help to get my shoulder joint ready for heavy lifting 

It’s great for flexibility and these type of movements will help your muscle bellies become fuller since elongation of many muscles are involved in doing a pullover 

Big muscles come from contracting AND stretching the muscle effectively and consistently under tension
